Another application of uranium salts is also mentioned, namely in the composition of some coloured lustres. For this purpose one first made a resinate which is than dissolved in a colophony and various essential oils such as oleum rosmarini, oleum lavendular, oleum spicae, oleum foeniculi and others. Uranium nitrate was used to produce brilliant, iridescent lustres of a yellow colour. For the necessary uranium resinate one dissolved the uranium nitrate and soft soap in a separate way. The solutions were then poured together under the forming of a resinate. This resinate must be washed, air-dried and could then be used.

