In 2001 a comprehensive article was published by Donna Strahan#footnote[Donna Strahan. 'Uranium in Glass, Glazes and Enamels: History, Identification and Handling'. Studies in Conservation, Vol.46, nr.3, 2001.]. The article is a survey of over 400 glass, ceramic and enamel objects from museum and private collections. It is an investigation for the extent of uranium colorants, mainly produced between 1830 till 1940. It shows that uranium colorant was widely used in glass and ceramic and also that little health risk was found from the uranium containing objects.

